#Text=Wikinews interviews Australian Paralympic skiers Toby Kane , Cameron Rahles Rahbula , and Mitchell Gourley
#Text=Friday , December 14 , 2012

#Text=Recently , Wikinews sat down with Australian standing Paralympic skiers Toby Kane , Cameron Rahles-Rahbula , and Mitchell Gourley who were in Vail , Colorado for a training camp for the start of this week 's IPC Nor-Am Cup .
#Text=Wikinews reporters LauraHale and Hawkeye7 interview Australian Paralympic skiers Cameron Rahles Rahbula , Mitchell Gourley , and Toby Kane
#Text=( ( Wikinews ) )
#Text=I 'm interviewing Cameron [ Rahles-Rahbula ] with a hyphenated last name , Mitchell Gourley , [ and ]
#Text=Toby Kane .
#Text=And they 're in Copper Mountain to compete with the IPC NorAm cup .
#Text=Cameron Rahles-Rahbula : Yes .
#Text=( ( WN ) ) So you guys can qualify for Sochi ?
#Text=Cameron Rahles-Rahbula : Not this race , but yeah ...
#Text=Toby Kane : Any races that we kind of do , I think we can qualify , but technically , for the APC it would have to be a world cup first to qualify .
#Text=( ( WN ) ) Where 's the world cups ?
#Text=Toby Kane : We have one this year in Italy , in Sestriere , and one in St Moritz , in Switzerland ...
#Text=Cameron Rahles-Rahbula : and one in Slovenia , in Maribor , and Russia ...
#Text=Mitchell Gourley : world championships in La Molina in Spain as well , and Russia , the test event is another world cup in Sochi .
#Text=( ( WN ) ) You guys are all skiers , right ?
#Text=all ( in unison ) : Yes .
#Text=( ( WN ) ) None of you , when they said " we 're doing snowboarding " , said " I want to jump ship and do snowboarding " ?
#Text=Toby Kane : No.
#Text=Mitchell Gourley : No.
#Text=Cameron Rahles-Rahbula : No.
#Text=( ( WN ) ) You all love the skiing . ( ( WN ) ) ( to Cameron Rahles-Rahbula ) :
#Text=What did you do to your chin [ which is taped up ] ?
#Text=Cameron Rahles-Rahbula : I had a crash last week , and I split my chin open .
#Text=I kneed myself here , so I had stitches .
#Text=Toby Kane : Thirteen stitches .
#Text=( ( WN ) ) Crashed skiing right ?
#Text=Cameron Rahles-Rahbula : Yeah .
#Text=Toby Kane :
#Text=Our physio probably took out five last night .
#Text=( ( WN ) ) As somebody who knows very little about Paralympic skiing , I have a question having watched it .
#Text=There seems to be three types skiiers : the ones who are in the monochairs , the ones who are blind , and the ones with amputations and the ones without arms .
#Text=I 've had this debate .
#Text=Who 's the craziest amongst you ?
#Text=The ones who ca n't see , the ones with no arms , or the ones on a mono-ski ?
#Text=Mitchell Gourley :
#Text=The completely blind people are a little nuts .
#Text=Toby Kane : A B1 is , blacked out goggles ...
#Text=Cameron Rahles-Rahbula : ... who just follows the sound of their guides .
#Text=So they 're probably , when it comes to speed events , in terms of fear level , that 's pretty intense .
#Text=( ( WN ) ) Not having arms , you do n't think , would be scarier ?
#Text=Mitchell Gourley : No.
#Text=Cameron Rahles-Rahbula : Yeah , but you can see where you are going .
#Text=When you have to trust the other person in front of you ...
#Text=Toby Kane : . . you have to be fairly crazy to do downhill in sit skis .

#Text=Cameron Rahles-Rahbula : Those guys , they start crashing , or they have a mistake , they ca n't recover in the same way a stand up can , so even though those classes are n't going as quickly , probably stand ups in general have a bit more control , and to recover .
